# Runtime OpenXR wire-protocol ABI pin.
#
# The DisplayXR OpenXR extension headers vendored under
#   Source/DisplayXRCore/Private/Native/openxr/XR_EXT_*.h
# are copied VERBATIM from DisplayXR/displayxr-runtime at the commit below.
# The `abi-guard` CI job (.github/workflows/lint.yml) fetches those headers at
# this ref and fails the build if the vendored copies have drifted — that drift
# is what caused the black-window regression (the Win32 window-binding struct
# grew fields the plugin's hand-mirror lacked) and the rendering-mode stride
# bug (#234).
#
# To adopt new runtime protocol: set this SHA to the new runtime commit, re-copy
# the four XR_EXT_*.h headers from displayxr-runtime at that SHA into
# Source/DisplayXRCore/Private/Native/openxr/, and rebuild. Keep this as a full
# 40-char commit SHA (immutable) — not a branch name.
#
# The pin is intentionally independent of the runtime's versions.json co-release
# matrix: this plugin is a downstream consumer of the wire protocol, released on
# its own cadence. This file is the only coupling between the two repos.

964277f5ec5fd727c9ac2a62ae90bd06178a7609
